com.wx.util.iterator

Class PeekIterator<Type>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wx.util.iterator.PeekIterator<Type>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<Type>

    public class PeekIterator<Type>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<Type>
    This class enhances any iterator by offering the ability to peek at the next value (ie. to access the next value without calling next or changing the state of the iterator).

    Note: The implementation may call the Iterator.next() method arbitrarily, if you need a clear control on when the Iterator.next() method of the underlying iterator is called, you should avoid using this wrapper.

      • peek

        public Type peek()
        Peek at the next value. The value returned by this method is the same as the value that will be returned by the next call to next().

        If this iterator does not have a next element, a NoSuchElementException is thrown.

        Calling this method does not affect the state of this iterator.

        Returns:
        The next element
        Throws:
        java.util.NoSuchElementException - if the iteration has no more elements
